## Relay Dispatcher

The Relay Dispatcher bridges your Claude Desktop agent to the shared LORE vector store. It is optional — the vector store and Gateway MCP work independently.

See [docs/infrastructure/switchboard-setup.md](docs/infrastructure/switchboard-setup.md) for platform-specific setup instructions (Mac/Linux, Windows, WSL+Windows).

### Starting the dispatcher

```bash
RELAY_AGENT_ID=<AGENT-NAME> \
DATABASE_URL=<your-postgres-connection-string> \
OPENAI_API_KEY=<key> \
MCP_DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID=lore-platform \
npx tsx src/relay/relay-dispatcher.ts
```

### Required environment variables

| Variable | Required | Notes |
|----------|----------|-------|
| `RELAY_AGENT_ID` | Yes | Your agent name — must be unique across the team |
| `DATABASE_URL` | Yes (or Supabase) | Postgres connection string (primary backend) |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Yes | Same as Gateway MCP |
| `SUPABASE_URL` | If no `DATABASE_URL` | Supabase fallback |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | If no `DATABASE_URL` | Required with `SUPABASE_URL` |
| `SWITCHBOARD_DATA_DIR` | WSL only | See setup guide |
| `MCP_DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID` | No | Falls back to `undefined` if absent |

### Notes

- The dispatcher must be running for automated relay capture to function.
- The dispatcher does NOT consume coordination messages. Only `capture_request` type messages are dispatched and cleared from the inbox.
- All captures go to the shared vector store under your agent name. See the setup guide for current limitations on private captures.
